25th October 1979 - 30th August 2013
Beloved wife, daughter, sister and friend
Forever loved, always missed, never forgotten
We all miss you so much
Jamie, Thomas and Spanky"Ė
ČSvetlana Grigorlan
13.08.1950 - 13.03.2019
If roses grew in Heaven, Lord please pick a bunch for me, place them in my
Mother's arms and tell her they're from me. Tell her I love her and miss her,
and when she turns smile, place a kiss upon her cheek and hold her for a while.
In loving memory of mum and wife that meant so much."Ķ
Źin Loving Memory of BRIAN MIST Naturalist and Conservationist
For his Work and Dedication to the Park
Who Died 8th May 2002 - Age 65
Sadly missed by his wife Rosie and son Bradley and all his friends"Ī
ĖA Battersea girl with a heart of gold. cared for her parents growing old
She would always give her time to share, with anyone feeling in despair
When troubles seem to fill their day, helped to clear their problems away
The world is now a sadder place, without her kind and smiling face
In memory of Mabel Gladys Coote 1922-2017"Ļ
ĢBRIAN BOTTING FRICS 1932 2014
First Chairman of the Friends of Battersea Park 1990- 1999
The Hungarian Oak opposite was planted in his memory
A great servant of the Park with a mischievous sense of fun"Ū
ŲIn Loving Memory of Georgi "Porgy" Todorov 1978 2005
"It's not the years in your life that count...
It's the life in your years" We will never forget your
smile, you are forever our inspiration. We miss you Porg x"Ū
